If the element is dynamically generated or loaded asynchronously, ensure that you're executing this code after the element has been added to the DOM. You can wrap your JavaScript code inside a `DOMContentLoaded` event listener to ensure it runs after the DOM is fully loaded:

```javascript
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
  // Your code here
});
```

Also, consider checking if there are any errors or warnings in the browser console that might give you more information about the issue.

